        <div class="section" id="complex_sentence_section">
            <div class="row section-header">
                <h2 style="display: inline; vertical-align: middle;">Mark Complex Sentences </h2>
                <!-- <a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#complex_sent_help" title="Click here for help" id="complexhelp"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-question-sign" aria-hidden="true"></span></a> -->
            </div>
            <div class="row section-alert alert-info alert-dismissible">
                <ul>
                    <li>To demarcate a sentence, you've need to click both the first and last words of that sentence</li>
                    <li>You'll observe matching colors for each pair of first and last words</li>
                    <!--<li>Please make sure that you are marking only for complex sentences</li>-->
                    <li>Need help? Head over <a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#complex_sent_help" title="Click here for help" id="complexhelp">here</a>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <!-- Modal -->
            <div class="modal fade" id="complex_sent_help" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="complexSentHelp">
              <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
                <div class="modal-content">
                  <div class="modal-header">
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
                    <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Tagging Complex Sentences</h4>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body">
                    <p>
                    To avoid ambiguity on a complex sentence, user can give the marking of each simple sentence present in the complex sentence<br>
                    Ex: for a sentence,<br>
                            राम ने कहा कि वह घर जाएगा |<br>
                        we will have provide the interface, <br>
                            <button>राम</button> <button>ने</button> <button>कहा</button> <button>कि</button> <button>वह</button> <button>घर</button> <button>जाएगा</button> <button>|</button> <br>
                        The simple sentences here are: राम ने कहा and वह घर जाएगा<br>
                        To tag the sentences, please click on the starting word and ending word of a sentence respectively for each sentence.<br>
                        After first sentence selection:<br>
                            <button style="background-color: red">राम</button> <button>ने</button> <button style="background-color: red">कहा</button> <button>कि</button> <button>वह</button> <button>घर</button> <button>जाएगा</button> <button>|</button> <br>
                        After second sentence selection:<br>
                            <button style="background-color: red">राम</button> <button>ने</button> <button style="background-color: red">कहा</button> <button>कि</button> <button style="background-color: green">वह</button> <button>घर</button> <button style="background-color: green">जाएगा</button> <button>|</button> <br>
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group" id="cst_text">
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-3 col-md-offset-5">
                    <button id="reset-brackets" class="btn btn-default" type="submit">Reset</button>
                    <button id="cst-submit" class="btn btn-primary section-submit" type="submit" data-uid="cst">Submit</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section" id="proper_noun_section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>Tag Proper Nouns</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row section-alert alert-info alert-dismissible">
                <ul>
                    <li>A parser always has problems in Named Entity Recognition</li>
                    <li>This tagging of named entity will improve the correctness of translation</li>
                    <li>Just click on all the named entities in your sentences, then press 'Done'</li>
                    <li>For a more detailed example and tutorial, please click <a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#proper_noun_help" title="Click here for help" id="properhelp">here</a>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <!-- Modal -->
            <div class="modal fade" id="proper_noun_help" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="properNounHelp">
              <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
                <div class="modal-content">
                  <div class="modal-header">
                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
                    <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Marking Proper Nouns</h4>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-body">
                    <p>
                        Some Content
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="modal-footer">
                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="form-group" id="cnt_text">
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-3 col-md-offset-5">
                    <button id="cnt-submit" class="btn btn-primary section-submit" type="submit" data-uid="cnt">Submit</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section" id="chunking_section">
            <div class="row section-header">
            <h2>
                Tag Word Chunks
            </h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row section-alert alert-info alert-dismissible">
                - A Chunk is defined as a collection of words that form a phrase. <br>
                - To mark a chunk, pick it's constituent wors and then click join. <BR>
                - Repeat this until you've marked all the chunks. <BR>
                - Need help? We've got you covered. Head over <a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#complex_sent_help" title="Click here for help" id="complexhelp">here</a> to see an example.<BR>
            </div>
            <div class="form-group" id="chnk_text">
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-7 col-md-offset-2">
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-danger" id="split-chunk">Split</button>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-warning" id="join-chunk" data-jointype="normal">Join</button>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default" id="join-chunk" data-jointype="compoundnoun">Join as Compound Noun</button>
                    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-default" id="join-chunk" data-jointype="complexpredicate">Join as Complex Predicate</button>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-2">
                    <button id="chnk-submit" class="btn btn-primary section-submit" type="submit" data-uid="chnk">Submit</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section" id="chl_section">
            <div class="section-header">
                <h2>Controlled Hindi Text</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row section-alert alert-info alert-dismissible">
                <ul>
                    <li>Corrections to the CHL form is essential for 'good' translation</li>
                    <li>To change the pratyaya of a word, just click and select the correct relation</li>
                    <li>To change the prakriti word, just click and write the correct form</li>
                    <li>For a more detailed example and tutorial, please click <a data-toggle="modal" data-target="#complex_sent_help" title="Click here for help" id="complexhelp">here</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <!--<button type="button" class="btn btn-default btn-xs" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#myModal" style="margin:5px;"> <b>Parser Output</b> </button> -->
            <!-- MODAL FOR ILPARSER OUTPUT-->
            <div class="modal fade" id="myModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel">
                <div class="modal-dialog" role="document" style="min-width:900px;">
                    <div class="modal-content">
                        <div class="modal-header">
                            <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"><span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span></button>
                            <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">ILPARSER OUTPUT</h4>
                        </div>
                        <div class="modal-body" id="parsed_sent">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row form-group" id="default_chl_text">
                Please Finish the above operations to see the chl form.
            </div>
            <div class="row" id="loading_image">
                <!-- <img src="images/ring-alt.gif" alt="Loading..."> -->
            </div>
            <div class="row" id="answer_row">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-offset-5 col-md-1">
                        <button class="btn btn-default btn-sm" id="undo"><img src="images/undo-icon.png">undo</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div id="output"></div>
                <button id="translate" class="btn btn-success">Translate</button>
                <div class="row" id="translated_output"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section" id="feedback_section">
